The paper focuses on improving the performance of object detection and classification tasks using deep neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed framework also involves the use of Long-short Term Memory (LSTM) and teacher-bounded loss design, which are techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. Additionally, the paper mentions the evaluation of the proposed method on dynamic scenes, which suggests a potential connection to robotics (cs.RO) and multimedia (cs.MM) research.
